            "answer_text": "I apologise for the quality of photo, and the writing isn\u2019t the best either, but I\u2019m currently on a moving coach, so this is the best I could do. If you want it in the middle of the word, I\u2019d go with something like this:  That says \u2018injured\u2019 if anyone can\u2019t recognise it. I do my \u2018r\u2019s in an odd way. Basically, you lead up to it like any other letter; there\u2019s a little slope up to the top, then you go down and around in the \u2018j\u2019 shape, but carry on looping all the way around so you can join it to the next letter. If you want to do it at the start of a word, I\u2019d do it like this:  That\u2019s says \u2018Just\u2019 if anyone\u2019s confused. You kind of do the same, using the little run up as the top stroke of the \u2018J\u2019 in a serif font, and looping around to start the next letter, only it\u2019s bigger. Hope this helped! ",
